recalls.Summary: Nissan North America, Inc. (Nissan) is recalling certain 2023-2024 Nissan Z vehicles.  The fasteners in the left-side front bumper reinforcement clip may loosen, which can prevent the pop-up engine hood from activating.
recalls.Consequence: A pop-up engine hood that does not activate and raise the rear end of the hood in a frontal pedestrian crash, can increase the risk of injury.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will tighten the fasteners, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed December 7, 2023.  Owners may contact Nissan's customer service at 1-800-867-7669.  Nissan's number for this recall is R23C8.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Nissan North America, Inc. (Nissan) is recalling certain 2023-2024 Nissan Z vehicles.  The connectors for the right-side pedestrian detection sensors may be reversed in the front bumper harness, which can prevent the pop-up engine hood from activating as intended.
recalls.Consequence: A pop-up engine hood that does not activate in a pedestrian crash can increase the risk of injury.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will replace the front bumper harness, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed December 11, 2024.  Owners may contact Nissan customer service at 1-800-867-7669.  Nissan's number for this recall is R24B6.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153) or go to nhtsa.gov.

complaints.summary: The contact owns a 2023 Nissan Z. The contact stated that while her son was driving at an undisclosed speed, upon coming to an abrupt stop, the hood suddenly popped open; obstructing the driver's view, prompting him to pull over to the shoulder of the roadway. The message "Collision Detected - Pop-up Activators Deployed" was displayed. No warning lights were illuminated. The vehicle was taken to the dealer, who diagnosed a failure with the active-hood pop-up pyro actuators. The vehicle was not repaired. After investigating the failure, the contact related the failure to NHTSA Campaign Number: 24V798000 (Structure, Electrical System); but the VIN was not included. The manufacturer was notified of the failure, and a case was opened. The failure mileage was 7,000.

issues.title: Transmission Jerky Shifting and Hesitation
issues.description: Multiple owners report jerky shifting, hesitation during acceleration, and rough transitions between gears in the 9-speed automatic transmission, particularly when cold or during low-speed maneuvers.
issues.fix_description: Software updates, transmission fluid change, or in severe cases transmission replacement under warranty
issues.prevention: Regular transmission service, allow proper warm-up time, avoid aggressive driving when cold

issues.title: Infotainment System Freezing and Black Screen
issues.description: Owners experience frequent freezing of the infotainment system, black screens, and unresponsive touchscreen controls, affecting navigation, audio, and climate control functions.
issues.fix_description: Software updates, system reset, or replacement of infotainment unit under warranty
issues.prevention: Regular software updates, avoid using system while vehicle is starting up

issues.title: Clutch Pedal Feel Issues in Manual Transmission
issues.description: Manual transmission models experience inconsistent clutch pedal feel, including spongy pedal, difficult engagement, and clutch slipping during spirited driving.
issues.fix_description: Clutch hydraulic system bleeding, clutch assembly replacement, or flywheel resurfacing
issues.prevention: Proper clutch technique, avoid riding the clutch, regular maintenance

issues.title: Paint Quality Issues and Premature Chipping
issues.description: Multiple reports of poor paint quality, including premature chipping, scratching easily, and paint defects from the factory, particularly on darker colored vehicles.
issues.fix_description: Touch-up paint, panel repainting, or full paint correction depending on severity
issues.prevention: Paint protection film, regular washing and waxing, avoid harsh chemicals

issues.title: Engine Oil Temperature Running High
issues.description: Owners report oil temperatures running higher than expected during normal driving conditions, with some experiencing oil temp warnings during track use or spirited driving.
symptoms: Engine running hot during performance driving
issues.fix_description: Additional oil cooling solutions, thermostat replacement, or cooling system upgrades
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes with high-quality oil, avoid prolonged high-RPM driving

issues.title: Door Handle Functionality Problems
issues.description: Some owners report issues with door handles becoming sticky, difficult to operate, or failing to properly engage, affecting both interior and exterior handles.
issues.fix_description: Lubrication of handle mechanisms, handle assembly replacement, or adjustment of door latch
issues.prevention: Regular cleaning and lubrication of door handles, gentle operation

issues.title: Tire Pressure Monitoring System False Alerts
issues.description: Multiple reports of TPMS sensors giving false low pressure warnings, displaying incorrect pressure readings, or failing to reset after tire pressure adjustment.
issues.fix_description: TPMS sensor replacement, system recalibration, or software updates
issues.prevention: Regular tire pressure checks, proper TPMS reset procedures after tire work

issues.title: Wind Noise at Highway Speeds
issues.description: Owners report excessive wind noise entering the cabin at highway speeds, particularly around the door seals and window areas, affecting comfort during long drives.
issues.fix_description: Door seal replacement, weatherstripping adjustment, or window alignment correction
issues.prevention: Regular inspection of door seals, proper door closing, avoid slamming doors

issues.title: Brake Pedal Feel Inconsistency
issues.description: Some owners report inconsistent brake pedal feel, including soft or spongy pedal, varying bite point, or reduced braking confidence, particularly after hard use.
issues.fix_description: Brake fluid flush, brake system bleeding, or brake component inspection and replacement
issues.prevention: Regular brake fluid changes, avoid overheating brakes, proper bedding procedure

issues.title: USB Port Connectivity Issues
issues.description: Multiple reports of USB ports not recognizing devices consistently, intermittent charging, or Android Auto/Apple CarPlay connection problems.
issues.fix_description: Software updates, USB port replacement, or wiring harness inspection
issues.prevention: Use quality USB cables, avoid forcing connections, keep ports clean

editorial.tagline: The Z is back, angrier than ever
editorial.hero_blurb: After years of waiting, Nissan finally delivered a proper successor to the legendary Z lineage. The new Z combines modern twin-turbo fury with old-school sports car purity, creating something that feels genuinely special in today's crossover-obsessed world.
editorial.essence: This is the Z car purists have been begging for - no hybrid complexity, no all-wheel-drive safety nets, just a naturally aspirated chassis with forced induction power. It's a proper sports car that prioritizes driver engagement over luxury amenities.
editorial.heritage: The Z nameplate spans over 50 years, from the original 240Z that shocked the world in 1970 through the beloved 300ZX of the '90s. This seventh generation carries forward that tradition of accessible performance and timeless proportions.
editorial.design_philosophy: Nissan's designers went full retro-futurism, channeling the original 240Z's long hood, short deck proportions while adding modern LED lighting and aggressive aero. The result is instantly recognizable as a Z car while looking thoroughly contemporary.
editorial.motorsport_history: Z cars dominated SCCA racing in the '70s and conquered IMSA in the '80s and '90s. The 300ZX won championships in both touring car and endurance racing, establishing the Z as a legitimate track weapon.
editorial.engine_character: The VR30DDTT is a masterpiece of modern turbo engineering - responsive like a naturally aspirated mill but with devastating midrange punch. It builds power smoothly from 2000 RPM and pulls hard to redline with minimal lag.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 6-speed manual is beautifully weighted with short, precise throws and a perfectly positioned clutch bite point. The 9-speed auto is surprisingly engaging with quick shifts and well-calibrated rev-matching.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: The chassis strikes an ideal balance between compliance and control, offering genuine feedback without punishing your spine. It rotates naturally under throttle and maintains composure even when pushed hard.
editorial.steering_feel: Electrically assisted but genuinely communicative, the steering loads up naturally through corners and provides real feedback about what the front tires are doing. Weight is perfectly calibrated for spirited driving.
editorial.brake_confidence: Strong, progressive pedal feel with excellent modulation and minimal fade during hard use. The brakes inspire confidence whether you're street driving or attacking your favorite back road.
editorial.sound_signature: A deep, purposeful rumble at idle that transforms into an angry howl under full acceleration. The twin turbos add subtle whistles and whooshes that remind you of the engineering underneath.
editorial.ideal_owner: Driving enthusiasts who want pure sports car thrills without supercar complexity or pricing. Perfect for weekend warriors who prioritize engagement over luxury.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Daily commuters seeking maximum comfort, tech-obsessed buyers wanting the latest infotainment, or anyone needing rear seat space or cargo capacity.
editorial.buyers_summary: The Z delivers authentic sports car character at a reasonable price, but interior quality and tech lag behind rivals. Buy it for the driving experience, not the cabin appointments.
